<br>
At 54, you should EASILY be able to clear either cave with one or two heals at most with Transon's and a few more if you don't. The most mana I've ever gone through in a single sweep was one and a half bubbles. (and this was because I nuked the Foreman, who is still dark blue to me at 53)<br>
<br>
Warning! The pathing in the cave closest to Katta Castellum zone is HIDEOUSLY screwed up! I tend to check the other cave first out of preference, so I con'd have to keep summon companion memed. If you DO use this cave, park your pet next to the NPC just inside and pull the two grimlings at the botom of the ramp and wait for them to run through the wall and back into the cave. (You WILL be hit as they just appear on top of you, but they don't hit too hard, so just move and let your pet finish them.) Once they're dead, walk down and past the support beams, Summon your pet to you and immediately set him on guard, or attack the next set. DO NOT let your pet walk to the bottom of the ramp, or it will path outside and dissapear for a while, possibly aggroing whatever happens to be standing nearby.  Once I'm past the entrance ramp, I usually stay inside to prevent having to cast SC repeatedly as I pass back and forth over the pathing SNAFU at the ramp bottom. (It's only 4 spawns anyway, there's 11 once you're inside the cave. PLENTY to keep you busy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
