Smithing - 110</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinghaovercast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Singha Overcast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#333333>(5/6/02 1:35:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=189.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where to make money at 54???</span><hr size=1> Maybe I'm just unlucky (I am) but I'm not seeing the great loot here. I slaughtered the grimlings nonstop for about an hour and a half last night. Putting on my sharpest outfit (charisma 112, indiff faction) I sold all the drops and ended up with 107pp. The bulk of that came from gems and weapon drops. I had one rune worth 6pp, the rest were 5gp at most, 3s more likely.<br>
<br>
I also got two blocks of acrylia and three small pieces of acrylia which I kept. So unless those together are worth 200pp I certainly didn't get anywhere near 300pp/hour.<br>
<br>
Oh, and the bottom of the first ramp is some of the worst pathing I've ever seen. Once I was inside I tagged one of the grimlings at the bottom of the first ramp. It was about 20 feet away from me at the time. It did a couple circles then disapeared into the wall never to be seen again. The poor thing is probably still wandering the zone.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <br>
 <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:Shadow(Color=#CC66FF, Direction=225)"><h4>Singha Overcast</h4></div> 
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinghaovercast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Singha Overcast</A> at: 5/6/02 4:40:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uansifiretosser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ansi Firetosser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#333333>(5/6/02 5:14:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=189.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where to make money at 54???</span><hr size=1> I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> still</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> swear by hill giants in Rathe.  Just get a pet and setup on top of the hill.  Snag them as soon as they pop.  You can do 2 or even 3 at a time if you make sure you brun down the one the pet has agroed.<br>
<br>
I use my water pet.  I know the air pet dodges better but I want the backstab to get the running giants quick when I'm kiting a giant in cirlces waiting for my pet to finish with the first one.  You do have your jboots right?  If not, it's worth the price to buy Sow potions for this.<br>
<br>
And it comes in waves, sometimes no giants for a few minutes straight then a bunch.  Just use that lack of giants to med back up.  Kill everything that moves near you.  Take all your regular backpacks and stick them in the bank and summon all those 10 slotters for the fine steel, destroy everything else.  destroy your copper and silver.  Get STR buffs and STR equipment OR have a horse.  (you're not slowed by being encumbered on a horse)<br>
<br>
Another key is headphones.  For me anyway, I don't move to look for pulls.  I listen for them.  The cyclops and Hill giants have very distinct sounds.  If I hear something, I move to it.  Otherwise I sit still and med sending my pet to kill the trash.<br>
<br>
I always DS anyone who walks by, less complainers that way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One other way of getting rid of the extra weight is bind at the base of the hill and use your Thurgadin gate potion to sell, then make a new one and gate back to Rathe.<br>
<br>
You DO have a Thurg potion right?  If not, make that your first camp, do Crystal Caverns and collect bricks and silks.<br>
<br>
Who cares about druids kiting down below the hill.  You get to kill the giants before they even move 5 steps.<br>
<br>
I've even had someone try to train me and my pet once, I thanked them very much for being my puller and killed the 2 giants in short order, hehe.  <br>
<br>
If I see a giant way on the other side of the hill, I leave it.  Or if one pops near a group, I let them have it.  It'll only be a matter of minutes if not seconds that one will pop right near me.  It seems the people who run back and forth looking for spawns miss more than just staying and waiting.  I'm very rarely full mana and when I am, I do my and the pet's buffs.<br>
<br>
If you get jumped by a cyclops or a second giant, try to train them on your pet by running through them, if not, just run it around in circles til your pet is done with the first giant.  If you get jumped by a skelly, either ignore it until the pet's done or blast it yourself channeling through the minor hits.<br>
<br>
The times I have had to run or gate, are when my pet is fighting a tainted and a second giant joins in, when the tainted drops the corrupted spawns right there and the pet will be standing there fighting the add making it a tough fight to do a dark blue corrupted and two other giants, sometimes you can do it, sometimes not.   Just remember it's better to take off running at the begining of a bad fight when your pet will give you time to get distance between you and the fight.<br>
<br>
Quite often, when I think things will go bad, I'll take off running with my pet targeted.  When he dies, I stop, cast a new pet, and the gaints will come to their deaths with a new pet handy.<br>
<br>
Do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> waste all your mana trying to save a pet in a tight spot, you need that 20% to get a new pet.<br>
<br>
I can make about 1500-2000 plat in 3 hours doing this.  I usually do this late at night (like 4am) when it thins out or very early in the morning.<br>
<br>
If you have only prime time to do this, then I've no idea how tough it might be for you since I avoid Rathe then.  I usually just do hill giants after my guild's events have wound down for the night. <p>Ansi Firetosser <BR> 50-ish Mage on Tunare <BR>  Proud member of the Echoes Guild<br><br><br>
